translated: Kamph, Sven Ludvig, office chief, Gothenburg, born on January 19, 1899 in Stockholm, the son of Per Gustaf Ludvig K. and his wife, Lundbom. Married on the 24th of a month with Karin du Rées. Children: Marianne born in 1925, Bengt in 1926, Birgit in 1931, Bertil in 1941. - Student at Bergslagen Railway in 1919, typist in 1922, office assistant in 1929, first office assistant in 1934, traffic inspector in 1938, first traffic inspector in 1940, office chief at the Traffic Department of Gothenburg-Dalarna-Gävle in the Commercial Division in Gothenburg since 1944. Member of the Swedish-Norwegian, Swedish-Danish, and Norwegian-Danish Tariff Committee from 1928 to 1932, secretary in the Bergslagen Railway Employees' Society from 1926 to 1929, its consumption association in 1930, the Swedish Iron Railway Association's railway tariff committee in 1939, auditor in the Bergslagen Railway pension fund from 1934 to 1936, chairman of the Association of Individual Railway Administration Employees from 1940 to 1946, section chief in the state price control committee from 1942 to 1944. RV01'kl..
